## üéØ Clinical Applications

### Primary Pattern & Manifestations
**Pattern**: Blood stasis obstructing head orifices and channels
**Key Symptoms**: Chronic headaches (fixed location), head trauma sequelae, memory problems, dizziness, tinnitus, blurred vision, facial paralysis, speech problems
**Tongue**: Purple or with purple spots
**Pulse**: Choppy or wiry and choppy

### Secondary Applications
- Post-concussion syndrome
- Chronic headaches from trauma
- Facial paralysis (Bell's palsy)
- Post-stroke rehabilitation
- Vascular dementia
- Chronic sinusitis with stasis

### Modern Clinical Uses
- Traumatic brain injury recovery
- Post-concussion syndrome
- Chronic headaches and migraines
- Post-stroke cognitive impairment
- Vascular dementia
- Chronic rhinosinusitis

